{
  "stem": "33.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, we were crammed into these cattle cars, cattle cars not meant for human transportation, obviously.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had no windows or no doors open.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were sitting on the floor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we were so many that I remember everybody couldn't really sit in the same time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some people had to stand and some people sat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We alternated.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Our journey began-- if I look at a map today, I think it could be done in about maybe 10 to 12 hours, but it took us 3 days.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We left on May the 31st of 1944.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I remember there was a little crack on the wall.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And one time when the train stopped, my father looked out and he could discern the name of the station.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And since he really knew his geography and I guess his railway situation very well, he said that this is a crucial point, because if at this point we're going to turn east, we're going into Poland.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If we turn west, that's good news, because we're going into Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I think we already had some kind of awareness that the bad camps are in Poland, not in Germany proper.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we did turn to the east.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were very lucky, because once a day our door was opened and we were given some fresh water and the toilet facility was taken away, emptied, and given back to us.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "As I later found out, a lot of people were not that lucky, because they travelled for as long as 10 days, 14 days, never being given fresh water or have the door open.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a lot of dead bodies would be taken off the train.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
